
	




#Enhancement (Add Metamagic)
Add (Specify) Metamagic (Various)
	SCHOOL:Transmutation	
Level:
Base Level Level of the spell to be affected
1-3 4-6 7-9 10-12
Requires 1 2 3 4
Then add the number of levels of metamagic
you wish to enhance the target spell with to
the listed base. For an extra +3 levels the
metamagic to be added may be left
unspecified until the spell is cast,
although the number of levels to be
added remains fixed.
	COMPS:V, S
	CASTTIME:One standard action
	RANGE:Touch, +1 level per additional range category
	TARGETAREA:Spellcasting creature touched
	DURATION:Special
	SAVEINFO:None
	SPELLRES:Yes (Harmless)
	DESC:See Text
	DESC:Add Metamagic simply adds the effects of a chosen metamagical feat or feats to another spell which is cast within the next three rounds.
#Such spells can be stacked.
#They are applied in the order in which they are cast and each successive spell applied must be potent enough to accommodate the enhanced level resulting from the proceeding spell. If your first selection is to add Silent Spell to your Fireball, your next Add Metamagic spell would have to be able to affect fourth level spells, since that is the neweffective level of your Fireball. For example, a spell which can affect a spell of up to L3 has a base level of 1. If it Enlarges the target spell - a +1 level metamagic - it becomes a level two spell. A spell which can add one level of any desired metamagic - Enlarge, Extend, Heighten (+1), Silent, Still, or any other +1 level metamagical modification - to a spell of up to L3 would be L5; a base of L1 for affecting a spell of up to L3, +1 for the +1 level of metamagic it adds, and +3 for being able to pick that modification at the time of casting. As a final example of stacking, if the original spell was L1, three of the basic enhancing spells from the prior paragraph could be applied - the first one raising it to L2, the second to L3, and the third to L4 - at which point it passes beyond the level at which basic enhancements can affect it.


